Security and Economic issues dominated discussions as the United States President Donald Trump formally received President Muhammadu Buhari at the White House. Adamu reports that a colourful and befitting diplomatic ceremony was held to welcome President Buhari who arrived he White House at about 12 o’clock Monday afternoon local time. President Trump warmly received the Nigerian leader at the forecourt of the Oval Office . The two leaders then retreated for talks on issues critical to the mutually beneficial relations between their countries. A.M Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. With a decade experience in Television journalism, and a graduate of University of Maiduguri. Tanimu also produces TV shows with NTA when not on Social media.